WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
To provide assistance in the form of discretionary donations to  individuals / organisations within a 30 mile radius of the village of Blofield, Norfolk provided the request has a medical, educational, religious, welfare or environmental resource connection. Donations made are not intended to form an on going relationship, (eg funding salaries) but more to meet specific needs (eg equipment, etc)

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
BLOFIELD, NORWICH, NR13 4SQ, Norfolk, Norfolk. ~95 staff; income on record £14,818,835.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Training + workflow review

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Community programmes involve volunteers, bookings, training registers and partner reporting.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Environmental charities often have seasonal volunteer peaks and grant-heavy funding. Practical AI for reporting drafts and volunteer comms is a common entry point.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
Field operations and land management systems are usually outside VAxAI direct delivery — focus on office coordination and reporting.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
THE R C SNELLING CHARITABLE TRUST shows environment & conservation delivery with material admin load — Reduce grant and project reporting assembly time

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Reduce grant and project reporting assembly time
• Review volunteer coordination workflows across sites
• AI workshop for comms and reporting teams

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

